<div class="col five-sm clear">
<h2 id="section-top">Overview</h2>
</div>
<div class="col four-sm">
</div>
<div class="col three-sm" id="ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_PlaceHolderMain_contentColumn1">
<div class="panel">
<div class="panel-content">
<div class="pad clear">
<div id="imageContent4494e64b48a94b5bbcaf9339bd50f0b4">
<div class="profile-pic">
<img alt="Christies Care logo" border="0" id="ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_PlaceHolderMain_column1Content_column1Content_SummaryAndPhotoModule_PhotoView_DisplayImage" src="/Services/UserControls/UploadHandlers/MediaServerHandler.ashx?id=221526"/>
</div>
</div>
<p>Rated OUTSTANDING by the CQC, Christies Care Ltd is a family owned specialist 24 hour live-in care agency.  </p>
<p>Founded in 1987 we have grown through word of mouth recommendations from satisfied clients.</p>
<p>Recipients of the Princess Royal Training Award in 2017.</p>
<p>We train all our carers to be companions, as well as to carry out the usual tasks of daily living such as cooking, laundry, light housework, and helping their clients get out and about. They give as much personal care and help with mobility as is needed.</p>
<p>We cover the whole of the UK and the Channel Islands, and our network of Local Area Advisors means that we always have a local expert to meet, advise and help our clients.</p>
<p>Who are our clients? Anybody who needs full time care. You may be convalescing after a stay in hospital, you might have dementia, have had a stroke, have a physical disability or learning difficulties or just want somebody to be there, to keep you safe.  </p>
<p>What does it cost? Typically, our clients pay between £1,000 and £1,500 a week for a live-in carer, which compares well to most good care homes.</p>
<p>Many of our clients receive continuing healthcare funding, or have all or part of their care paid for by the local authority.</p></div>
